{"type":"data","nodes":[null,{"type":"data","data":[{"content":1},[2,27,49,67],{"title":3,"titleHtml":4,"description":5,"authors":6,"yyyymmdd":10,"thumbnail":11,"thumbnailAlt":20,"tags":21,"slug":25,"src":26},"Wispack – An R package for warped sigmoidal Poisson-process mixed-effects modeling","\u003Cstrong>Wispack\u003C/strong> – An R package for warped sigmoidal Poisson-process mixed-effects modeling","Wispack (pronounced “wisp package” or “wisp pack”) is an R package for testing for between-group effects on spatial variation in spatial transcriptomics data. As such variation is often functional, these can be thought of as functional spatial effects (FSE).",[7,8,9],"Michael Barkasi","Cody Nhan Pham","Hysell V. Oviedo","20260515",{"sources":12,"img":16},{"avif":13,"webp":14,"png":15},"/_app/immutable/assets/wisp_art.C4gfk67H.avif 1280w, /_app/immutable/assets/wisp_art.Diq1UNFj.avif 640w, /_app/immutable/assets/wisp_art.CsKyC6cz.avif 400w","/_app/immutable/assets/wisp_art.DHAsRJH0.webp 1280w, /_app/immutable/assets/wisp_art.B37rQYK_.webp 640w, /_app/immutable/assets/wisp_art.CYS2HJD1.webp 400w","/_app/immutable/assets/wisp_art.Dx-12CjU.png 1280w, /_app/immutable/assets/wisp_art.qcJdhmcc.png 640w, /_app/immutable/assets/wisp_art.B_auW9u9.png 400w",{"src":17,"w":18,"h":19},"/_app/immutable/assets/wisp_art.Dx-12CjU.png",1280,809,"Artistic rendering of wisp model",[22,23,24],"MERFISH","software","spatial transcriptomics","wispack","/src/content/tech-n-tools/wispack/wispack.svx",{"title":28,"titleHtml":29,"description":30,"authors":31,"yyyymmdd":32,"thumbnail":33,"thumbnailAlt":42,"tags":43,"slug":47,"src":48},"neuronsDG – Modelling neurons via dichotomized Gaussians","\u003Cstrong>neuronsDG\u003C/strong> – Modelling neurons via dichotomized Gaussians","\u003Cstrong>neuronsDG\u003C/strong> is an R/C++ package for simulating neurons, currently under development at Oviedo Lab. The package is built around the core object class neuron, a C++ class accessible through R via Rcpp modules and wrappers. This class is meant for modeling the spiking of single neurons with dichotomized Gaussians.",[7],"20260420",{"sources":34,"img":38},{"avif":35,"webp":36,"png":37},"/_app/immutable/assets/DG_autocorr.Ls56p9eg.avif 1182w, /_app/immutable/assets/DG_autocorr.CEbzCKj5.avif 640w, /_app/immutable/assets/DG_autocorr.BKRxoLS6.avif 400w","/_app/immutable/assets/DG_autocorr.DxZBo7K2.webp 1182w, /_app/immutable/assets/DG_autocorr.Bn8Fw7pY.webp 640w, /_app/immutable/assets/DG_autocorr.CN-dW4lg.webp 400w","/_app/immutable/assets/DG_autocorr.VGhCoifk.png 1182w, /_app/immutable/assets/DG_autocorr.BA0skihj.png 640w, /_app/immutable/assets/DG_autocorr.BAIbd_8l.png 400w",{"src":39,"w":40,"h":41},"/_app/immutable/assets/DG_autocorr.VGhCoifk.png",1182,695,"Artistic overlay of spike trains with autocorrelation and a dichotomized Gaussian with covariance. This package uses the latter to generate simulations of the former.",[44,45,46],"circuit mapping","simulation","SNNs","neuronsDG","/src/content/tech-n-tools/neuronsDG/neuronDG.svx",{"title":50,"titleHtml":51,"description":52,"authors":53,"yyyymmdd":54,"thumbnail":55,"thumbnailAlt":63,"tags":64,"slug":65,"src":66},"DACx – Digital Auditory Cortex","\u003Cstrong>DACx\u003C/strong> – Digital Auditory Cortex","\u003Cstrong>DACx\u003C/strong> is an R/C++ package for running biologically realistic simulations of the mammalian auditory cortex – a “digital twin”. \u003Ca href=\"https://oviedolab.org/DACx/articles/tutorial_network_topology\" rel=\"nofollow\">Network topologies\u003C/a> are built from clusters of cells, called \u003Cem>nodes\u003C/em>, arrayed in three dimensions and connected using circuit motifs. \u003Ca href=\"https://oviedolab.org/DACx/articles/tutorial_SGT\" rel=\"nofollow\">Network activity\u003C/a> is simulated using an expanded version of the growth-transform (GT) membrane voltage time derivative introduced by \u003Ca href=\"https://doi.org/10.3389/fnins.2020.00425\" rel=\"nofollow\">Gangopadhyay and Chakrabartty\u003C/a>.",[7],"20260419",{"sources":56,"img":60},{"avif":57,"webp":58,"png":59},"/_app/immutable/assets/demo_network.BF-f1oqH.avif 1280w, /_app/immutable/assets/demo_network.BY98CV68.avif 640w, /_app/immutable/assets/demo_network.Djh_UbgT.avif 400w","/_app/immutable/assets/demo_network.B1SD4FNz.webp 1280w, /_app/immutable/assets/demo_network.CJfTUaZR.webp 640w, /_app/immutable/assets/demo_network.Simo0n1Q.webp 400w","/_app/immutable/assets/demo_network.D2P8ZUj9.png 1280w, /_app/immutable/assets/demo_network.DZeqlYet.png 640w, /_app/immutable/assets/demo_network.D3R_akIi.png 400w",{"src":61,"w":18,"h":62},"/_app/immutable/assets/demo_network.D2P8ZUj9.png",1074,"Example plot of 3D network topology producable with DACx.",[44,45,46],"DACx","/src/content/tech-n-tools/DACx/DACx.svx",{"title":68,"titleHtml":68,"description":69,"authors":70,"yyyymmdd":71,"thumbnail":72,"thumbnailAlt":80,"tags":81,"slug":83,"src":84},"Quality Control Algorithm for MERFISH Software","Quality control algorithm and software that can be used to improve MERFISH runs.",[7,8,9],"20260204",{"sources":73,"img":76},{"avif":74,"webp":75},"/_app/immutable/assets/ppv-by-gene-barcode.BXisyvir.avif 354w","/_app/immutable/assets/ppv-by-gene-barcode.PrhoPpGg.webp 354w",{"src":77,"w":78,"h":79},"/_app/immutable/assets/ppv-by-gene-barcode.B-D6K4Qk.png",354,207,"Example of Estimated Precision (PPV) by gene barcode for a MERFISH run",[22,82,23,24],"QC","qc-algorithm-for-merfish-software","/src/content/tech-n-tools/qc-algorithm-for-merfish-software/qc-algo-merfish.svx"],"uses":{}},{"type":"data","data":[{"content":1},{"title":2,"titleHtml":3,"description":4,"authors":5,"yyyymmdd":9,"thumbnail":10,"thumbnailAlt":19,"tags":20,"slug":24,"src":25},"Wispack – An R package for warped sigmoidal Poisson-process mixed-effects modeling","\u003Cstrong>Wispack\u003C/strong> – An R package for warped sigmoidal Poisson-process mixed-effects modeling","Wispack (pronounced “wisp package” or “wisp pack”) is an R package for testing for between-group effects on spatial variation in spatial transcriptomics data. As such variation is often functional, these can be thought of as functional spatial effects (FSE).",[6,7,8],"Michael Barkasi","Cody Nhan Pham","Hysell V. Oviedo","20260515",{"sources":11,"img":15},{"avif":12,"webp":13,"png":14},"/_app/immutable/assets/wisp_art.C4gfk67H.avif 1280w, /_app/immutable/assets/wisp_art.Diq1UNFj.avif 640w, /_app/immutable/assets/wisp_art.CsKyC6cz.avif 400w","/_app/immutable/assets/wisp_art.DHAsRJH0.webp 1280w, /_app/immutable/assets/wisp_art.B37rQYK_.webp 640w, /_app/immutable/assets/wisp_art.CYS2HJD1.webp 400w","/_app/immutable/assets/wisp_art.Dx-12CjU.png 1280w, /_app/immutable/assets/wisp_art.qcJdhmcc.png 640w, /_app/immutable/assets/wisp_art.B_auW9u9.png 400w",{"src":16,"w":17,"h":18},"/_app/immutable/assets/wisp_art.Dx-12CjU.png",1280,809,"Artistic rendering of wisp model",[21,22,23],"MERFISH","software","spatial transcriptomics","wispack","/src/content/tech-n-tools/wispack/wispack.svx"],"uses":{"params":["content"],"parent":1}}]}
